{
  "id": "RAW_ba7aa851",
  "title": "EP196：云负载均衡器速查表",
  "url": "https://blog.bytebytego.com/p/ep196-cloud-load-balancer-cheat-sheet",
  "date": "2026-01-03 16:31:02",
  "author": "ByteByteGo",
  "siteName": "ByteByteGo Newsletter",
  "content": "<html>\n <head></head>\n <body>\n  <div dir=\"auto\" class=\"body markup\">\n   <h2 class=\"header-anchor-post\">\n    <br>\n   </h2>\n   <p>This week’s system design refresher:</p>\n   <ul>\n    <li>\n     <p>Cloud Load Balancer Cheat Sheet</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n     <p>How CQRS Works?</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n     <p>How does Docker Work?</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n     <p>6 Practical AWS Lambda Application Patterns You Must Know</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n     <p>Containerization Explained: From Build to Runtime</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n     <p><span>🚀</span><a href=\"https://bytebyteai.com/\" rel=\"\"> Learn AI in the New Year: Become an AI Engineer Cohort 3 Now Open</a></p>\n    </li>\n   </ul>\n   <p>Efficient load balancing is vital for optimizing the performance and availability of your applications in the cloud.</p>\n   <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n    <figure>\n     <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!hXRV!,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe99863c7-7ab7-4f61-9961-af7e4c6ee64f.png\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\" rel=\"\" class=\"image-link image2 can-restack\"> \n      <div class=\"image2-inset can-restack\">\n       <picture><img src=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!hXRV!,w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe99863c7-7ab7-4f61-9961-af7e4c6ee64f.png\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/e99863c7-7ab7-4f61-9961-af7e4c6ee64f.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:null,&quot;width&quot;:null,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:2864350,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:&quot;https://blog.bytebytego.com/i/183283151?img=https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe99863c7-7ab7-4f61-9961-af7e4c6ee64f.png&quot;,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null,&quot;offset&quot;:false}\" alt=\"\" sizes=\"100vw\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"sizing-normal\"></picture>\n      </div> \n     </a>\n    </figure>\n   </div>\n   <p></p>\n   <p>However, managing load balancers can be overwhelming, given the various types and configuration options available.</p>\n   <p>In today's multi-cloud landscape, mastering load balancing is essential to ensure seamless user experiences and maximize resource utilization, especially when orchestrating applications across multiple cloud providers. Having the right knowledge is key to overcoming these challenges and achieving consistent, reliable application delivery.</p>\n   <p>In selecting the appropriate load balancer type, it's essential to consider factors such as application traffic patterns, scalability requirements, and security considerations. By carefully evaluating your specific use case, you can make informed decisions that enhance your cloud infrastructure's efficiency and reliability.</p>\n   <p>This Cloud Load Balancer cheat sheet would help you in simplifying the decision-making process and helping you implement the most effective load balancing strategy for your cloud-based applications.</p>\n   <p><span>Over to you: What factors do you believe are most crucial in choosing the right load balancer type for your applications?</span>\n    <br></p>\n   <h2 class=\"header-anchor-post\">How CQRS Works?\n    <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-alignItems-center pc-position-absolute pc-reset header-anchor-parent\">\n     <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-contents pc-reset pubTheme-yiXxQA\">\n      <button type=\"button\" aria-label=\"Link\" data-href=\"https://blog.bytebytego.com/i/183283151/how-cqrs-works\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft iconButton-mq_Et5 iconButtonBase-dJGHgN buttonBase-GK1x3M buttonStyle-r7yGCK size_sm-G3LciD priority_secondary-S63h9o\" tabindex=\"0\">\n       <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"18\" height=\"18\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-link\">\n        <path d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\"></path><path d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\"></path>\n       </svg>\n      </button>\n     </div>\n    </div></h2>\n   <p>CQRS (Command Query Responsibility Segregation) separates write (Command) and read (Query) operations for better scalability and maintainability.</p>\n   <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n    <figure>\n     <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!XvtW!,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1ded3402-4eb5-4818-861f-7661f1cefe82.tif\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\" rel=\"\" class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img can-restack\"> \n      <div class=\"image2-inset can-restack\">\n       <picture><img src=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!XvtW!,w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1ded3402-4eb5-4818-861f-7661f1cefe82.tif\" width=\"800\" height=\"939\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/1ded3402-4eb5-4818-861f-7661f1cefe82.tif&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:939,&quot;width&quot;:800,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:3008358,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/tiff&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:&quot;https://blog.bytebytego.com/i/183283151?img=https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1ded3402-4eb5-4818-861f-7661f1cefe82.tif&quot;,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null,&quot;offset&quot;:false}\" alt=\"\" sizes=\"100vw\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"sizing-normal\"></picture>\n       <div class=\"image-link-expand\">\n        <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-gap-8 pc-reset\">\n         <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container restack-image\">\n          <svg role=\"img\" style=\"height:20px;width:20px\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\" fill=\"none\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" stroke=\"var(--color-fg-primary)\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\">\n           <g>\n            <title></title><path d=\"M2.53001 7.81595C3.49179 4.73911 6.43281 2.5 9.91173 2.5C13.1684 2.5 15.9537 4.46214 17.0852 7.23684L17.6179 8.67647M17.6179 8.67647L18.5002 4.26471M17.6179 8.67647L13.6473 6.91176M17.4995 12.1841C16.5378 15.2609 13.5967 17.5 10.1178 17.5C6.86118 17.5 4.07589 15.5379 2.94432 12.7632L2.41165 11.3235M2.41165 11.3235L1.5293 15.7353M2.41165 11.3235L6.38224 13.0882\"></path>\n           </g>\n          </svg>\n         </button>\n         <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container view-image\">\n          <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2 lucide-maximize-2\">\n           <polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" x2=\"14\" y1=\"3\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" x2=\"10\" y1=\"21\" y2=\"14\"></line>\n          </svg>\n         </button>\n        </div>\n       </div>\n      </div> \n     </a>\n    </figure>\n   </div>\n   <p>Here’s how it works:</p>\n   <ol>\n    <li>\n     <p>The client sends a command to update the system state. A Command Handler validates and executes logic using the Domain Model.</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n     <p>Changes are saved in the Write Database and can also be saved to an Event Store. Events are emitted to update the Read Model asynchronously.</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n     <p>The projections are stored in the Read Database. This database is eventually consistent with the Write Database.</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n     <p>On the query side, the client sends a query to retrieve data.</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n     <p>A Query Handler fetches data from the Read Database, which contains precomputed projections.</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n     <p>Results are returned to the client without hitting the write model or the write database.</p>\n    </li>\n   </ol>\n   <p>Over to you: What else will you add to understand CQRS?</p>\n   <h2 class=\"header-anchor-post\">How does Docker Work?\n    <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-alignItems-center pc-position-absolute pc-reset header-anchor-parent\">\n     <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-contents pc-reset pubTheme-yiXxQA\">\n      <button type=\"button\" aria-label=\"Link\" data-href=\"https://blog.bytebytego.com/i/183283151/how-does-docker-work\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft iconButton-mq_Et5 iconButtonBase-dJGHgN buttonBase-GK1x3M buttonStyle-r7yGCK size_sm-G3LciD priority_secondary-S63h9o\" tabindex=\"0\">\n       <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"18\" height=\"18\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-link\">\n        <path d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\"></path><path d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\"></path>\n       </svg>\n      </button>\n     </div>\n    </div></h2>\n   <p>Docker’s architecture is built around three main components that work together to build, distribute, and run containers.</p>\n   <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n    <figure>\n     <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!SUjA!,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd91a5538-a69e-468c-bf83-058bb78753ca_2360x2770.png\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\" rel=\"\" class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img can-restack\"> \n      <div class=\"image2-inset can-restack\">\n       <picture><img src=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!SUjA!,w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd91a5538-a69e-468c-bf83-058bb78753ca_2360x2770.png\" width=\"1456\" height=\"1709\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/d91a5538-a69e-468c-bf83-058bb78753ca_2360x2770.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:1709,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;Image&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null,&quot;offset&quot;:false}\" alt=\"Image\" title=\"Image\" sizes=\"100vw\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"sizing-normal\"></picture>\n       <div class=\"image-link-expand\">\n        <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-gap-8 pc-reset\">\n         <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container restack-image\">\n          <svg role=\"img\" style=\"height:20px;width:20px\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\" fill=\"none\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" stroke=\"var(--color-fg-primary)\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\">\n           <g>\n            <title></title><path d=\"M2.53001 7.81595C3.49179 4.73911 6.43281 2.5 9.91173 2.5C13.1684 2.5 15.9537 4.46214 17.0852 7.23684L17.6179 8.67647M17.6179 8.67647L18.5002 4.26471M17.6179 8.67647L13.6473 6.91176M17.4995 12.1841C16.5378 15.2609 13.5967 17.5 10.1178 17.5C6.86118 17.5 4.07589 15.5379 2.94432 12.7632L2.41165 11.3235M2.41165 11.3235L1.5293 15.7353M2.41165 11.3235L6.38224 13.0882\"></path>\n           </g>\n          </svg>\n         </button>\n         <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container view-image\">\n          <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2 lucide-maximize-2\">\n           <polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" x2=\"14\" y1=\"3\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" x2=\"10\" y1=\"21\" y2=\"14\"></line>\n          </svg>\n         </button>\n        </div>\n       </div>\n      </div> \n     </a>\n    </figure>\n   </div>\n   <ol>\n    <li>\n     <p><span>Docker Client</span>\n      <br>\n      <span>This is the interface through which users interact with Docker. It sends commands (such as build, pull, run, push) to the Docker Daemon using the Docker API.</span></p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n     <p><span>Docker Host</span>\n      <br>\n      <span>This is where the Docker Daemon runs. It manages images, containers, networks, and volumes, and is responsible for building and running applications.</span></p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n     <p><span>Docker Registry</span>\n      <br>\n      <span>The storage system for Docker images. Public registries like Docker Hub or private registries allow pulling and pushing images.</span></p>\n    </li>\n   </ol>\n   <p>Over to you: Do you use Docker in your projects?</p>\n   <h2 class=\"header-anchor-post\">6 Practical AWS Lambda Application Patterns You Must Know\n    <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-alignItems-center pc-position-absolute pc-reset header-anchor-parent\">\n     <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-contents pc-reset pubTheme-yiXxQA\">\n      <button type=\"button\" aria-label=\"Link\" data-href=\"https://blog.bytebytego.com/i/183283151/practical-aws-lambda-application-patterns-you-must-know\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft iconButton-mq_Et5 iconButtonBase-dJGHgN buttonBase-GK1x3M buttonStyle-r7yGCK size_sm-G3LciD priority_secondary-S63h9o\" tabindex=\"0\">\n       <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"18\" height=\"18\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-link\">\n        <path d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\"></path><path d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\"></path>\n       </svg>\n      </button>\n     </div>\n    </div></h2>\n   <p>AWS Lambda pioneered the serverless paradigm, allowing developers to run code without provisioning, managing, or scaling servers. Let’s look at a few practical application patterns you can implement using Lambda.</p>\n   <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n    <figure>\n     <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!U3Mj!,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F12efbba7-28b6-48e9-bf80-c6f59d82eacd_2250x2814.jpeg\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\" rel=\"\" class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img can-restack\"> \n      <div class=\"image2-inset can-restack\">\n       <picture><img src=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!U3Mj!,w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F12efbba7-28b6-48e9-bf80-c6f59d82eacd_2250x2814.jpeg\" width=\"1456\" height=\"1821\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/12efbba7-28b6-48e9-bf80-c6f59d82eacd_2250x2814.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:1821,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;Image&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null,&quot;offset&quot;:false}\" alt=\"Image\" title=\"Image\" sizes=\"100vw\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"sizing-normal\"></picture>\n       <div class=\"image-link-expand\">\n        <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-gap-8 pc-reset\">\n         <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container restack-image\">\n          <svg role=\"img\" style=\"height:20px;width:20px\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\" fill=\"none\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" stroke=\"var(--color-fg-primary)\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\">\n           <g>\n            <title></title><path d=\"M2.53001 7.81595C3.49179 4.73911 6.43281 2.5 9.91173 2.5C13.1684 2.5 15.9537 4.46214 17.0852 7.23684L17.6179 8.67647M17.6179 8.67647L18.5002 4.26471M17.6179 8.67647L13.6473 6.91176M17.4995 12.1841C16.5378 15.2609 13.5967 17.5 10.1178 17.5C6.86118 17.5 4.07589 15.5379 2.94432 12.7632L2.41165 11.3235M2.41165 11.3235L1.5293 15.7353M2.41165 11.3235L6.38224 13.0882\"></path>\n           </g>\n          </svg>\n         </button>\n         <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container view-image\">\n          <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2 lucide-maximize-2\">\n           <polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" x2=\"14\" y1=\"3\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" x2=\"10\" y1=\"21\" y2=\"14\"></line>\n          </svg>\n         </button>\n        </div>\n       </div>\n      </div> \n     </a>\n    </figure>\n   </div>\n   <ol>\n    <li>\n     <p><span>On-Demand Media Transformation</span>\n      <br>\n      <span>Whenever a user requests an image from S3 in a format that isn’t available, an on-demand transformation can be done using AWS Lambda.</span></p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n     <p><span>Multiple Data Format from Single Source</span>\n      <br>\n      <span>AWS Lambda can work with SNS to create a layer where data can be processed in the required format before sending to the storage layer.</span></p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n     <p><span>Real-time Data Processing</span>\n      <br>\n      <span>Create a Kinesis stream and corresponding Lambda function to process different types of data (clickstream, logs, location tracking, or transactions) from your application.</span></p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n     <p><span>Change Data Capture</span>\n      <br>\n      <span>Amazon DynamoDB can be integrated with AWS Lambda to respond to database events (inserts, updates, and deletes) in the DynamoDB streams.</span></p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n     <p><span>Serverless Image Processing</span>\n      <br>\n      <span>Process and recognize images in a serverless manner using AWS Lambda. Integrate with AWS Step Functions for better workflow management.</span></p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n     <p><span>Automated Stored Procedure</span>\n      <br>\n      <span>Invoke Lambda as a stored procedure to trigger functionality before/after some operations are performed on a particular database table.</span></p>\n    </li>\n   </ol>\n   <p>Over to you: Have you used AWS Lambda in your project?</p>\n   <h2 class=\"header-anchor-post\">Containerization Explained: From Build to Runtime\n    <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-alignItems-center pc-position-absolute pc-reset header-anchor-parent\">\n     <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-contents pc-reset pubTheme-yiXxQA\">\n      <button type=\"button\" aria-label=\"Link\" data-href=\"https://blog.bytebytego.com/i/183283151/containerization-explained-from-build-to-runtime\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft iconButton-mq_Et5 iconButtonBase-dJGHgN buttonBase-GK1x3M buttonStyle-r7yGCK size_sm-G3LciD priority_secondary-S63h9o\" tabindex=\"0\">\n       <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"18\" height=\"18\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-link\">\n        <path d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\"></path><path d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\"></path>\n       </svg>\n      </button>\n     </div>\n    </div></h2>\n   <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n    <figure>\n     <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!4qBZ!,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff0945414-9cea-4e64-8dd4-3abcc404f73e_2360x2960.png\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\" rel=\"\" class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img can-restack\"> \n      <div class=\"image2-inset can-restack\">\n       <picture><img src=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!4qBZ!,w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff0945414-9cea-4e64-8dd4-3abcc404f73e_2360x2960.png\" width=\"1456\" height=\"1826\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/f0945414-9cea-4e64-8dd4-3abcc404f73e_2360x2960.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:1826,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;Image&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null,&quot;offset&quot;:false}\" alt=\"Image\" title=\"Image\" sizes=\"100vw\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"sizing-normal\"></picture>\n       <div class=\"image-link-expand\">\n        <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-gap-8 pc-reset\">\n         <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container restack-image\">\n          <svg role=\"img\" style=\"height:20px;width:20px\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\" fill=\"none\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" stroke=\"var(--color-fg-primary)\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\">\n           <g>\n            <title></title><path d=\"M2.53001 7.81595C3.49179 4.73911 6.43281 2.5 9.91173 2.5C13.1684 2.5 15.9537 4.46214 17.0852 7.23684L17.6179 8.67647M17.6179 8.67647L18.5002 4.26471M17.6179 8.67647L13.6473 6.91176M17.4995 12.1841C16.5378 15.2609 13.5967 17.5 10.1178 17.5C6.86118 17.5 4.07589 15.5379 2.94432 12.7632L2.41165 11.3235M2.41165 11.3235L1.5293 15.7353M2.41165 11.3235L6.38224 13.0882\"></path>\n           </g>\n          </svg>\n         </button>\n         <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container view-image\">\n          <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2 lucide-maximize-2\">\n           <polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" x2=\"14\" y1=\"3\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" x2=\"10\" y1=\"21\" y2=\"14\"></line>\n          </svg>\n         </button>\n        </div>\n       </div>\n      </div> \n     </a>\n    </figure>\n   </div>\n   <p>“Build once, run anywhere.” That’s the promise of containerization, and here’s how it actually works:</p>\n   <p>Build Flow: Everything starts with a Dockerfile, which defines how your app should be built. When you run docker build, it creates a Docker Image containing:</p>\n   <ul>\n    <li>\n     <p>Your code</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n     <p>The required dependencies</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n     <p>Necessary libraries</p>\n    </li>\n   </ul>\n   <p>This image is portable. You can move it across environments, and it’ll behave the same way, whether on your local machine, a CI server, or in the cloud.</p>\n   <p>Runtime Architecture: When you run the image, it becomes a Container, an isolated environment that executes the application. Multiple containers can run on the same host, each with its own filesystem, process space, and network stack.</p>\n   <p>The Container Engine (like Docker, containerd, CRI-O, or Podman) manages:</p>\n   <ul>\n    <li>\n     <p>The container lifecycle</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n     <p>Networking and isolation</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n     <p>Resource allocation</p>\n    </li>\n   </ul>\n   <p>All containers share the Host OS kernel, sitting on top of the hardware. That’s how containerization achieves both consistency and efficiency, light like processes, but isolated like VMs.</p>\n   <p>Over to you: When deploying apps, do you prefer Docker, containerd, or Podman, and why?</p>\n   <h2 class=\"header-anchor-post\"><strong>🚀 Learn AI in the New Year: Become an AI Engineer Cohort 3 Now Open</strong>\n    <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-alignItems-center pc-position-absolute pc-reset header-anchor-parent\">\n     <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-contents pc-reset pubTheme-yiXxQA\">\n      <button type=\"button\" aria-label=\"Link\" data-href=\"https://blog.bytebytego.com/i/183283151/learn-ai-in-the-new-year-become-an-ai-engineer-cohort-now-open\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft iconButton-mq_Et5 iconButtonBase-dJGHgN buttonBase-GK1x3M buttonStyle-r7yGCK size_sm-G3LciD priority_secondary-S63h9o\" tabindex=\"0\">\n       <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"18\" height=\"18\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-link\">\n        <path d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\"></path><path d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\"></path>\n       </svg>\n      </button>\n     </div>\n    </div></h2>\n   <p>After the amazing success of Cohorts 1 and 2 (with close to 1,000 engineers joining and building real AI skills), we are excited to announce the launch of Cohort 3 of Become an AI Engineer!</p>\n   <p data-attrs=\"{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://bytebyteai.com&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Check it out Here&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:&quot;button-wrapper&quot;}\" data-component-name=\"ButtonCreateButton\" class=\"button-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://bytebyteai.com\" rel=\"\" class=\"button primary button-wrapper\"><span>Check it out Here</span></a></p>\n   <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n    <figure>\n     <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://bytebyteai.com/\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\" rel=\"\" class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img can-restack\"> \n      <div class=\"image2-inset can-restack\">\n       <picture><img src=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!KAgE!,w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbfb33f0a-196e-4b38-8bc5-647dbdc1e8c3_2360x2920.png\" width=\"1456\" height=\"1801\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/bfb33f0a-196e-4b38-8bc5-647dbdc1e8c3_2360x2920.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:1801,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:763360,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:&quot;https://bytebyteai.com/&quot;,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:&quot;https://blog.bytebytego.com/i/182634749?img=https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbfb33f0a-196e-4b38-8bc5-647dbdc1e8c3_2360x2920.png&quot;,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null,&quot;offset&quot;:false}\" alt=\"\" title=\"\" sizes=\"100vw\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"sizing-normal\"></picture>\n       <div class=\"image-link-expand\">\n        <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-gap-8 pc-reset\">\n         <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container restack-image\">\n          <svg role=\"img\" style=\"height:20px;width:20px\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\" fill=\"none\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" stroke=\"var(--color-fg-primary)\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\">\n           <g>\n            <title></title><path d=\"M2.53001 7.81595C3.49179 4.73911 6.43281 2.5 9.91173 2.5C13.1684 2.5 15.9537 4.46214 17.0852 7.23684L17.6179 8.67647M17.6179 8.67647L18.5002 4.26471M17.6179 8.67647L13.6473 6.91176M17.4995 12.1841C16.5378 15.2609 13.5967 17.5 10.1178 17.5C6.86118 17.5 4.07589 15.5379 2.94432 12.7632L2.41165 11.3235M2.41165 11.3235L1.5293 15.7353M2.41165 11.3235L6.38224 13.0882\"></path>\n           </g>\n          </svg>\n         </button>\n         <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container view-image\">\n          <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2 lucide-maximize-2\">\n           <polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" x2=\"14\" y1=\"3\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" x2=\"10\" y1=\"21\" y2=\"14\"></line>\n          </svg>\n         </button>\n        </div>\n       </div>\n      </div> \n     </a>\n    </figure>\n   </div>\n   <p data-attrs=\"{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://bytebyteai.com&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Check it out Here&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:&quot;button-wrapper&quot;}\" data-component-name=\"ButtonCreateButton\" class=\"button-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://bytebyteai.com\" rel=\"\" class=\"button primary button-wrapper\"><span>Check it out Here</span></a></p>\n  </div>\n </body>\n</html>",
  "aiSummary": "本期通讯简要回顾了云负载均衡、CQRS、Docker 架构以及实用的 AWS Lambda 模式，并包含了一款 AI 代码审查工具和 AI 工程课程的推广内容。",
  "oneSentenceSummary": "本期通讯简要回顾了云负载均衡、CQRS、Docker 架构以及实用的 AWS Lambda 模式，并包含了一款 AI 代码审查工具和 AI 工程课程的推广内容。",
  "summary": "本期通讯汇集了多个系统设计的简要复习资料，主要聚焦于通用软件工程概念。内容包括云负载均衡器的简要介绍，解释了其重要性及选择因素；随后概述了命令查询职责分离（CQRS）架构模式，详细说明了其分离读写操作的工作流；同时解释了 Docker 的架构组件和工作流，涵盖客户端、宿主机和注册表；最后展示了 AWS Lambda 的六种实际应用模式，如按需媒体转换、实时数据处理和变更数据捕获。文章还包含 CodeRabbit（一款 AI 代码审查副驾驶工具）的显著赞助广告以及一门 AI 工程课程的广告。",
  "mainPoints": [
    {
      "point": "云负载均衡器是提升应用性能和可用性的核心工具，需要根据流量、可扩展性和安全需求进行仔细选择。",
      "explanation": "在现代云环境中，有效的负载均衡对于确保无缝的用户体验以及优化多云部署中的资源利用率至关重要，且有多种配置选项可供选择。"
    },
    {
      "point": "CQRS 是一种通过分离命令（写）和查询（读）职责来增强可扩展性和可维护性的架构模式。",
      "explanation": "它涉及客户端发送更新写入数据库的命令，通过事件异步更新读取数据库，随后客户端从读取数据库中查询预计算的投影数据。"
    },
    {
      "point": "Docker 的运行依赖于客户端-宿主机-注册表架构，用于构建、分发和运行容器。",
      "explanation": "Docker 客户端向宿主机上的 Docker Daemon 发送命令，后者负责管理容器、镜像和网络，而 Docker Registry 则用于存储容器镜像。"
    },
    {
      "point": "AWS Lambda 实现了无服务器计算，为各种应用需求提供了实用的模式。",
      "explanation": "Lambda 的核心用例包括按需媒体转换、数据格式处理、通过 Kinesis 进行实时数据处理、配合 DynamoDB 进行变更数据捕获、无服务器图像处理以及自动化存储过程。"
    },
    {
      "point": "以 Docker 为代表的容器化技术通过共享宿主机内核的隔离环境，提供了应用的一致性和高效性。",
      "explanation": "它允许应用程序通过 Dockerfile 构建为镜像并实现一次构建、随处运行，由容器引擎负责管理生命周期、网络和资源分配，同时共享宿主机操作系统内核。"
    }
  ],
  "keyQuotes": [
